{"name": "ccplot", "metadata": {"name": "ccplot", "version": "2.1.4", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Console", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Natural Language :: English", "Operating System :: MacOS :: MacOS X", "Operating System :: Microsoft :: Windows", "Operating System :: POSIX", "Programming Language :: C", "Programming Language :: Cython", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Atmospheric Science", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Visualization"], "home_page": "http://www.ccplot.org/", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "CloudSat and CALIPSO plotting tool", "upload_time": 1694196144}, "documentation": ["ccplot is an open source command-line program for\n    plotting profile, layer and earth view data sets from CloudSat, CALIPSO\n    and Aqua MODIS products.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "ccplot.autostr", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ccplot.autostr.autostr", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "arg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "ccplot.autostr.Autostr", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "ccplot.autostr.Autostr._autostr", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "s", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "ccplot.autostr.Autostr._encoding", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.autostr.Autostr._mode", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "setup", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python3"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.WIN_HDF_DIR", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.WIN_HDFEOS_DIR", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.numpy_include_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.numpy_include_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.HDF_DIR", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.HDFEOS_DIR", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdf_libraries", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdf_include_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdf_library_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdfeos_libraries", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdfeos_include_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdfeos_library_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.dlls", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.package_data", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdf_libraries", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdf_include_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdf_library_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdfeos_libraries", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdfeos_include_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.hdfeos_library_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.package_data", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ccplot", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ccplot.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ccplot.utils.calipso_time2dt", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "time", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Convert float in format yymmdd.ffffffff to datetime."]}, {"name": "ccplot.utils.cloudsat_time2dt", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "time", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "start_time", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Convert time in seconds since start_time to datetime."]}, {"name": "ccplot.utils.dimmap", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "n", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "off", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "inc", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "axis", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "modulus", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Perform dimension mapping on array `x` along axis `axis`\nwith offset `off` and increment `inc`. The axis is extended to the length\n`n`. Intermediate values are interpolated by linear interpolation.\nValues outside of `x` are extrapolated by linear gradient\nat the boundaries.\n\nOptional argument `modulus` causes dimmap\nto operate in modular arithmetic with the given modulus. In such case\nintermediate values are interpolated over the shortest path between\nthe adjacent values in `x`.\n\n# Examples\n\n```pycon\n>>> dimmap(np.array([350, 5, 20, 10, 350]), 30, 4, 5, 0, 360)\narray([ 338.,  341.,  344.,  347.,  350.,  353.,  356.,  359.,    2.,\n          5.,    8.,   11.,   14.,   17.,   20.,   18.,   16.,   14.,\n         12.,   10.,    6.,    2.,  358.,  354.,  350.,  346.,  342.,\n        338.,  334.,  330.])\n```\n\n# References\n\n- HDF-EOS Library User's Guide for the ECS Project, Volume 1:\n\nOverview and Examples\n"]}, {"name": "ccplot.utils.cmap", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Load colormap from file. The expected format of the file is:\n\n    BOUNDS\n    from1 to1 step1\n    from2 to2 step2\n    [...]\n\n    TICKS\n    from1 to1 step1\n    from2 to2 step2\n    [...]\n\n    COLORS\n    r1 g1 b1\n    r2 g2 b2\n    [...]\n\n    UNDER_OVER_BAD_COLORS\n    ro go bo\n    ru gu bu\n    rb gb bb\n\nwhere fromn, ton, stepn are floating point numbers as would be supplied\nto numpy.arange, and rn, gn, bn are the color components the n-th color\nstripe. Components are expected to be in base 10 format (0-255).\nUNDER_OVER_BAD_COLORS section specifies colors to be used for\nover, under and bad (masked) values, in that order."]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ccplot.config", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "ccplot.config.sharepath", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.config.sharepath", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.config.sharepath", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot", "documentation": ["!/usr/bin/env python3", "ccplot", "This file is a part of ccplot: CloudSat and CALIPSO plotting tool.", "Copyright (c) 2009-2023 Peter Kuma", "This software is provided under the terms of a 2-clause BSD licence:", "Redistribution and use in source and binary forms, with or without", "modification, are permitted provided that the following conditions are met:", "1. Redistributions of source code must retain the above copyright notice,", "this list of conditions and the following disclaimer.", "2. Redistributions in binary form must reproduce the above copyright", "notice, this list of conditions and the following disclaimer", "in the documentation and/or other materials provided with", "the distribution.", "THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED BY THE CCPLOT PROJECT ``AS IS'' AND ANY EXPRESS", "OR IMPLIED WARRANTIES, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, THE IMPLIED WARRANTIES", "OF MERCHANTABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE ARE DISCLAIMED.", "IN NO EVENT SHALL THE CCPLOT PROJECT OR CONTRIBUTORS BE LIABLE FOR ANY", "DIRECT, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, EXEMPLARY, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES", "(INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, PROCUREMENT OF SUBSTITUTE GOODS OR SERVICES;", "LOSS OF USE, DATA, OR PROFITS; OR BUSINESS INTERRUPTION) HOWEVER CAUSED", "AND ON ANY THEORY OF LIABILITY, WHETHER IN CONTRACT, STRICT LIABILITY,", "OR TORT (INCLUDING NEGLIGENCE OR OTHERWISE) ARISING IN ANY WAY OUT OF THE", "USE OF THIS SOFTWARE, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGE.", "We don't want the annoying KeyboadInterrupt exception on Control-C."], "functions": [{"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.fail", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "s", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Early functions."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.fsencode", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.sdecode", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.report_memory", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Functions."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.warn", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "s", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.info", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "s", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.autodetect", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "product", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Autodetect product type. Recognition is done by feature detection.\nSupported types:\n\n    calipso-profile         CALIPSO profile products\n    calipso-layer           CALIPSO layer products\n    cloudsat-2b-geoprof     CloudSat 2B-GEOPROF\n    modis-swath-l1b         MODIS L1B Swath"]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.norm_index", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "a", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "b", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.modis_band_wavelength", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "band", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.radiance2temp", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "L", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lamb", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Converts radiace to temperature by inverse Planck's law.\n\nArguments:\n    L       -- radiance in W m^-2 m^-1\n    lamb    -- wavelength in m\n\nReturns:\n    Temerature in K."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.version", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Prints version information and exits with 0."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.usage", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Prints usage information and exits the program with return value of 1."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.help_and_exit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Prints help and exits the program with return value of 0."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.help_options", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.help_projections", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.parse_extent", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["\"Parses extent in format from..to or from..to,from..to and returns\nan instance of class HorizontalExtent. Raises ValueError on parsing\nerror.\n\nArguments:\n    text -- text to be parsed\n\nReturns:\n    Instance of HorizontalExtent."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.parse_options", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "argv", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parses command-line arguments.\n\nArguments:\n    argv -- array of command-line arguments\n\nReturns:\n    instance of Options"]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.loadcolormap", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["\"Returns a tuple of matplotlib colormap, matplotlib norm,\nand a list of ticks loaded from the file filename in format:\n\nBOUNDS\nfrom1 to1 step1\nfrom2 to2 step2\n...\n\nTICKS\nfrom1 to1 step1\nfrom2 to2 step2\n\nCOLORS\nr1 g1 b1\nr2 g2 b2\n...\n\nUNDER_OVER_BAD_COLORS\nro go bo\nru gu bu\nrb gb bb\n\nWhere fromn, ton, stepn are floating point numbers as would be supplied\nto numpy.arange, and rn, gn, bn are the color components the n-th color\nstripe. Components are expected to be in base10 format (0-255).\nUNDER_OVER_BAD_COLORS section specifies colors to be used for\nover, under and bad (masked) values in that order.\n\nArguments:\n    filename    -- name of the colormap file\n    name        -- name for the matplotlib colormap object\n\nReturns:\n    A tuple of: instance of ListedColormap, instance of BoundaryNorm, ticks."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.print_info", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "product", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Print information about a product."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.calipso_time2dt", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "time", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "start_time", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Converts a float in format yymmdd.ffffffff to a instance of python\ndatetime class.\n\nArguments:\n    time        -- float in format yymmdd.ffffffff\n    start_time  -- ignored\n\nReturns:\n    An instance of datetime."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.cloudsat_time2dt", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "time", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "start_time", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Converts time in seconds to a instance of python datetime class.\n\nArguments:\n    time        -- seconds from start_time\n    start_time  -- python datetime\n\nReturns:\n    An instance of datetime."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.fit_colorbar", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "axes", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "aspect", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "space", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "padding", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Creates new axes for a colorbar at the expense of main axes.\n\nArguments:\n    fig     -- an instance of mpl.Figure\n    axes    -- an instance of mpl.Axes\n    aspect  -- colorbar axes aspect ratio\n\nReturns:\n    An instance of mpl.Axes."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.stripstr", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "s1", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "s2", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.lon2str", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "lonf", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "degree", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.lat2str", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "latf", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "degree", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.setup_lonlat_axes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "axes", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lon", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lat", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.get_axes_bounds", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "axes", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.resize_figure", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "figw", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "figh", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.expand_axes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "axes", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "width", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "height", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "padding", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.new_axes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "x", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "y", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "width", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "height", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "padding", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.time2ray", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "t", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "time", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "time2dt", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns index i of 1-dimensional array time whose value of\ntime2dt(time[i]) best matches dt.time instance t. Returns -1 if time\nis empty."]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.lonlat2ray", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "lonextent", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "latextent", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lon", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lat", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.figure_title", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "opts", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "title", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.plot_profile", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "what", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fname", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "product", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "axes", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "hextent", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "vextent", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "aspect", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "colormap", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "norm", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "ticks", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "radius", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "opts", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Plot profile or layer as specified by argument what.\n\nArguments:\n    what            -- plot type string\n    fname           -- file name\n    product         -- product file to read data from\n    fig             -- matplotlib Figure instance to draw onto\n    axes            -- matplotlib Axes instance to draw onto\n    hextent         -- an instance of HorizontalExtent\n    vextent         -- vertical extent, a pair of low and high boundary\n                       in meters\n    aspect          -- aspect ratio in s per km\n    colormap        -- matplotlib Colormap instance\n    norm            -- matplotlib Normalize instance\n    ticks           -- a list of ticks to be drawn on colorbar"]}, {"name": "ccplot.bin.ccplot.plot_orbit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "fnames", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "products", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fig", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "axes", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "hextent", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "band", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "band_mode", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "proj", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "proj_opts", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "clipped", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "colormap", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name":